@node SharewareNotice "Shareware Notice"
The Nightlight Team are very proud to present their first AGA Games called
Step Five. This concept is simply an enhanced and improved version of the
well known Tetris Game. The Code, Gfx and Musics are not so easy to make
and we hope that the general design enjoyed to the most of you. 


This Game was released under the concept of "Shareware". We have released
a test version that may be spread to give you a hint on the program's
abilities. You may use the programs for a period of up to 15 days for
testing purposes. After that, you have to register.


By cooperating with this concept, you help to ensure continued development
of this product and the possibility to see others product we want to
create in the futur.
@endnode
@Node Registering "Registering for the game"
To register simply send us a letter with your remark or anything else with
at least US $10 or 15 DM or 50 French Francs ( PLEASE try to send in
priority the money in French Francs). We thanks you very much in advance.


We will then register you as a user, and immediately mail you a branded 3,5"
disk with the complete Version of this amazing AGA Game. Please allow a few
weeks for delivery (typically much less).


Even though it does entail a slight risk, I encurage you to simply send
actual currency in plain old envelopes. Naturally, postal money orders
(those reddish cardboard forms :) are also welcome (again, only issued in
French Francs). Ask at your local post office.
@EndNode
